STATE OF HAWAII ' ' * H.D. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO DISCRIMINATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAH:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the vigilance of
2 individual citizens can keep communities safe through the
3 reporting of witnessed criminal conduct to law enforcement.
4 However, the legislature also finds that in certain
5 circumstances, individuals have misused the ability to summon
6 law enforcement officers against persons of protected classes
7 without reason to suspect a crime is being committed.
8 The purpose of this Act is to give any person injured by
9 discriminatory reporting to a law enforcement officer recourse
10 through civil action.
11 SECTION 2. The Hawaii Revised Statutes is amended by
12 adding a new chapter to be appropriately designated and to read
13 as follows:
14 "CHAPTER
15 DISCRIMINATORY REPORTING TO A LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER
16 § -1 Discriminatory reporting; law enforcement officer;
17 civil remedy. (a) Any person who knowingly causes a law
2025-2538 SB116 HDl HMSO 1
