Page 2 S.B. NO.
1 enforcement officer to come to a location to contact a person on
2 the basis of the person's actual or perceived race, color,
3 ancestry, ethnicity, national origin, place of birth, sex, age,
4 religion, disability, sexual orientation, or gender identity or
5 expression with the specific intent to:
6 (1) Infringe upon the person's rights under the Hawaii
7 State Constitution or United States Constitution;
8 (2) Discriminate against the person;
9 (3) Cause the person to feel harassed, humiliated, or
10 embarrassed;
11 (4) Cause the person to be expelled from a place that the
12 person is lawfully located;
13 (5) Damage the person's reputation or standing within the
14 community; or
15 (6) Damage the person's financial, economic, consumer, or
16 business prospects or interests,
17 shall be liable in a civil action or proceeding.
18 (b) Any person injured by a violation of subsection (a)
19 may bring a civil action in a court of competent jurisdiction in
20 the State for injunctive relief; payment for damages, which may
21 include punitive damages; or other appropriate relief. If, in
2025-2538 SB116 HDl HMSO
Page 3
S.B. NO.
