1 the action, the court finds that the defendant is violating or
2 has violated subsection (a), the court shall enjoin the
3 defendant from a continuance thereof. It shall not be necessary
4 that actual damages to the plaintiff be alleged or proved in
5 order to obtain the injunction.
6 (c) If the judgment is for the plaintiff, the plaintiff
7 shall be awarded damages of no less than $1,000 plus attorneys'
8 fees and costs.
9 § -2 Guidance. The department of law enforcement, in
10 consultation with the Hawaii civil rights commission, shall
11 provide guidance to the public on the civil liability and
12 remedies available for discriminatory reporting to a law
13 enforcement officer pursuant to this chapter."
14 SECTION 3. Section 368-1, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 "§368-1 Purpose and intent. The legislature finds and
17 declares that the practice of discrimination because of race,
18 color, religion, age, sex, including gender identity or
19 expression, sexual orientation, marital status, national origin,
20 place of birth, ancestry, or disability in employment, housing,
21 public accommodations, or access to services receiving state
2025-2538 SB116 HDl HMSO
