1 financial assistance is against public policy. It is the
2 purpose of this chapter to provide a mechanism that provides for
3 a uniform procedure for the enforcement of the State's
4 discrimination laws. It is the legislature's intent to preserve
5 all existing rights and remedies under such laws."
6 SECTION 4. New statutory material is underscored.
7 SECTION 5. This Act shall take effect on September 1,
8 2025.
